To interface two microphones with the ESP32-WROOM using the ADC with DMA, you can use the following code as a starting point. Please note that this code assumes that you have two microphones with the same specifications connected to the ESP32-WROOM.
```cpp
#include <driver/adc.h>
#include <driver/dma.h>

// Define the microphone pins
#define MIC_A 25 // Replace with the GPIO number for the first microphone (VCC)
#define MIC_B 23 // Replace with the GPIO number for the second microphone (VCC)

// ADC and DMA parameters
#define ADC_NUM 14 // Use ADC channel 14 (PA14) for microphone input
#define SAMpling_FreQuency 8000 // Set the microphone sampling frequency to 8 kHz
#define CHANNEL_A 0 // Channel for the first microphone
#define CHANNEL_B 1 // Channel for the second microphone

// Circular buffer parameters
#define BUFFER_SIZE 1024 // Set the buffer size to 1024 samples
#define BUFFER_LEN 256 // Set the number of samples per channel to 256

// Structure to hold microphone data
typedef struct
{
  int16_t channel_a[BUFFER_LEN];
  int16_t channel_b[BUFFER_LEN];
  uint32_t length;
  uint32_t index;
} MicrophoneData;

MicrophoneData mic_data;

// Initialize the microphones
void microphone_init()
{
  // Configure ADC
  adc_config_width(ADC_WIDTH_BIT_12);
  adc_config_channel_offset(ADC_CHANNEL_OFFSET_NONE);
  adc_config_ sampling_rate(SAMpling_FreQuency);
  adc_config_resolution(ADC_RESOLUTION_12BIT);

  // Configure ADC channel
  adc_channel_config(ADC_CHANNEL_A, ADC_CHANNEL_INPUT, ADC_CHANNEL_PASSTHROUGH);
  adc_channel_config(ADC_CHANNEL_B, ADC_CHANNEL_INPUT, ADC_CHANNEL_PASSTHROUGH);

  // Configure GPIO pins for microphones
  gpio_set_direction(MIC_A, GPIO_MODE_ANALOG);
  gpio_set_direction(MIC_B, GPIO_MODE_ANALOG);

  // Enable ADC
  adc_start();
}

// Read microphone data using DMA
void read_adc_data()
{
  // Configure DMA
  dma_channel_config(DMA_CHANNEL_0, DMA_PERIPHERAL_TO_MEMORY, ADC_DMA_CHANNEL, DMA_PRIORITY_HIGH, 0);

  // Start DMA transfer
  dma_start(DMA_CHANNEL_0);

  // Wait for DMA transfer to complete
  dma_wait(DMA_CHANNEL_0);

  // Read ADC data
  mic_data.channel_a[mic_data.index] = adc_get_raw(ADC_CHANNEL_A);
  mic_data.channel_b[mic_data.index] = adc_get_raw(ADC_CHANNEL_B);

  // Increment index
  mic_data.index = (mic_data.index + 1) % BUFFER_LEN;
}

void setup()
{
  // Initialize the microphones
  microphone_init();

  // Configure DMA
  dma_channel_config(DMA_CHANNEL_0, DMA_PERIPHERAL_TO_MEMORY, ADC_DMA_CHANNEL, DMA_PRIORITY_HIGH, 0);

  // Enable DMA
  dma_enable(DMA_CHANNEL_0);
}

void loop()
{
  // Read ADC data using DMA
  read_adc_data();

  // Process the microphone data
  // ...
}
```
This code initializes two microphones and configures the ADC to sample from them with a sampling frequency of 8 kHz. The ADC data is then read using DMA into a circular buffer. You can modify the `read_adc_data()` function to use a double buffer instead of a circular buffer if you prefer.

Please note that this code is just a starting point and requires further processing of the microphone data to implement the desired audio processing features. You will need to develop the remaining logic based on the requirements of your project.

