```
for (size_t v = 0; v < triVerts.size() / 3; ++v) {
    // Check if the vertex is part of an edge that is shared by two different faces
    bool isBoundaryVertex = false;
    for (size_t f = 0; f < numFaces; ++f) {
        size_t offset = 3 * f;
        if (triVerts[offset] == v || triVerts[offset + 1] == v || triVerts[offset + 2] == v) {
            if (triVerts[offset] == triVerts[offset + 3] ||
                triVerts[offset] == triVerts[offset + 6] ||
                triVerts[offset + 1] == triVerts[offset + 3] ||
                triVerts[offset + 1] == triVerts[offset + 5] ||
                triVerts[offset + 2] == triVerts[offset + 4] ||
                triVerts[offset + 2] == triVerts[offset + 6]) {
                isBoundaryVertex = true;
                break;
            }
        }
    }

    // If the vertex is a boundary vertex, add an entry to newMergeFrom and newMergeTo
    if (isBoundaryVertex) {
        for (size_t f = 0; f < numFaces; ++f) {
            size_t offset = 3 * f;
            if (triVerts[offset] == v || triVerts[offset + 1] == v || triVerts[offset + 2] == v) {
                newMergeFrom.push_back(v);
                if (triVerts[offset] == v) {
                    newMergeTo.push_back(triVerts[offset + 3]);
                } else if (triVerts[offset + 1] == v) {
                    newMergeTo.push_back(triVerts[offset + 5]);
                } else {
                    newMergeTo.push_back(triVerts[offset + 6]);
                }
                break;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

This code first checks if a vertex is part of an edge that is shared by two different faces. If so, it iterates over all the faces in the mesh and finds the two faces that share the edge. It then adds an entry to `newMergeFrom` and `newMergeTo` to indicate that the two vertices in the shared edge should be merged in the new mesh.

Note that this code assumes that the input mesh is a manifold mesh, i.e., it has no boundary edges or boundary vertices. If the input mesh has boundary edges or vertices, then the code will need to be modified accordingly.

