Here is how you can make a list of API calls using Promise.all and get the results:

```js
const apiCalls = [
  fetch('https://api.com/users'),
  fetch('https://api.com/posts'),
  fetch('https://api.com/comments')
];

Promise.all(apiCalls)
  .then(responses => {
    // responses is an array of the response objects for each API call
    return Promise.all(responses.map(res => res.json()));  
  })
  .then(results => {
    // results is an array of the JSON results for each API call  
    const users = results[0];
    const posts = results[1];
    const comments = results[2];

    // Use the results...
  });
```

Promise.all takes an array of promises as input, and returns a promise that resolves when all the input promises have resolved.

We map the array of responses to call .json() on each response, which returns a promise of the JSON result.

Then we use Promise.all again to wait for all the .json() promises to resolve, and we get an array of the JSON results.

Hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.

