```
var promises = [];
promises.push(fetch('API1.json').then(response => response.json()));
promises.push(fetch('API2.json').then(response => response.json()));
// And so on
Promise.all(promises).then(results => {
  // results is an array of the results
  console.log(results);
});
```
This code creates an array of promises, then uses Promise.all() to wait for all of them to resolve, then logs the results of each of the API calls in the results array.

